00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

1
00:00:49,385 --> 00:00:50,505
Fun, don't!

2
00:00:51,345 --> 00:00:52,265
Mom!

3
00:00:52,345 --> 00:00:55,465
Fun, why weren't you more careful?
You know Mom's back hurts.

4
00:00:55,545 --> 00:00:57,305
I've been thinking about this for a while

5
00:00:57,385 --> 00:00:59,825
that I want you
to move into a retirement home.

6
00:00:59,905 --> 00:01:03,065
Oon, do you know that every piece
of furniture and every item in this house

7
00:01:03,745 --> 00:01:05,424
<i>means so much to your mom?</i>

8
00:01:05,505 --> 00:01:08,945
<i>Let's bring this photo back to life.</i>

9
00:01:14,665 --> 00:01:16,585
Why am I so sore?

10
00:01:18,145 --> 00:01:19,945
All I did today was drive.

11
00:01:21,505 --> 00:01:23,865
Did you forget what we did today?

12
00:01:26,065 --> 00:01:28,945
Oh, right, the vegetable garden.

13
00:01:44,185 --> 00:01:45,505
I really love this photo.

14
00:01:45,585 --> 00:01:47,985
It just feels so warm.

15
00:01:49,225 --> 00:01:50,345
I like it too.

16
00:01:58,065 --> 00:01:59,545
Thank you.

17
00:02:00,865 --> 00:02:02,225
For what?

18
00:02:03,385 --> 00:02:04,865
For this.

19
00:02:07,425 --> 00:02:08,505
For what?

20
00:02:10,425 --> 00:02:12,145
For this.

21
00:02:13,585 --> 00:02:14,705
If it's this…

22
00:02:16,225 --> 00:02:17,705
that's not enough.

23
00:02:30,225 --> 00:02:31,465
It has to be more than that.

24
00:02:45,185 --> 00:02:46,905
As you wish.

25
00:03:06,585 --> 00:03:08,065
Aren't you still sore?

26
00:03:09,665 --> 00:03:10,825
Not anymore.

27
00:05:35,105 --> 00:05:37,025
-Yeah?
-<i>Hey.</i>

28
00:05:37,105 --> 00:05:38,705
<i>Where are you?</i>

29
00:05:39,585 --> 00:05:41,305
Alright. I'm coming, I'm coming.

30
00:05:41,385 --> 00:05:42,665
Don't tell me you just woke up.

31
00:05:42,745 --> 00:05:44,105
Gotta go.

32
00:05:46,785 --> 00:05:49,505
Fun, we're late. It's nine already.

33
00:05:50,425 --> 00:05:52,585
Ugh, I'm late too.
I have to go to the office today.

34
00:05:59,745 --> 00:06:01,465
For the fourth floor,

35
00:06:01,545 --> 00:06:05,345
the interior flooring will use
hollow-core slabs like on the third floor.

36
00:06:05,425 --> 00:06:08,425
The exterior will be
cast-in-place concrete to prevent leakage

37
00:06:08,505 --> 00:06:10,545
and ensure structural safety,

38
00:06:10,625 --> 00:06:12,585
as per your earlier comments.

39
00:06:12,665 --> 00:06:16,025
Good. I like it. Let's proceed with this.

40
00:06:16,105 --> 00:06:17,585
Thank you.

41
00:06:18,305 --> 00:06:19,985
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

42
00:06:20,065 --> 00:06:21,065
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

43
00:06:30,185 --> 00:06:31,705
IF YOU'RE FREE, PLEASE CALL ME.

44
00:06:37,985 --> 00:06:39,145
This one's grey.

45
00:06:39,225 --> 00:06:41,185
OON-OON

46
00:06:42,585 --> 00:06:45,025
-Go ahead, take it.
-Thank you.

47
00:06:49,945 --> 00:06:51,145
Did your meeting finish?

48
00:06:51,225 --> 00:06:52,745
Just finished.

49
00:06:52,825 --> 00:06:55,385
<i>Oon-oon, what time will you get off today?</i>

50
00:06:55,465 --> 00:06:57,825
I'll be busy with a client this evening,

51
00:06:57,905 --> 00:06:59,705
but I need to pick up my laundry.

52
00:06:59,785 --> 00:07:02,145
<i>I might not make it</i>
<i>before the shop closes.</i>

53
00:07:02,225 --> 00:07:05,065
It's okay. I'll stop by
and pick it up on my way home.

54
00:07:05,745 --> 00:07:08,385
Thank you. See you at home.

55
00:07:08,465 --> 00:07:09,505
See you.

56
00:07:14,745 --> 00:07:17,745
Hey, Oon, are you free?
Help me pick something.

57
00:07:19,825 --> 00:07:21,025
What is it?

58
00:07:21,105 --> 00:07:23,865
I can't decide between these two.

59
00:07:24,625 --> 00:07:25,825
Which one do you like?

60
00:07:26,425 --> 00:07:28,825
I like this one.

61
00:07:30,465 --> 00:07:31,985
But I like this one.

62
00:07:33,025 --> 00:07:35,345
-I can't choose.
-What's wrong with you?

63
00:07:35,425 --> 00:07:38,625
Are you in a rush today?
Stay and help me decide.

64
00:07:41,825 --> 00:07:43,985
I can, but make it quick.

65
00:07:44,065 --> 00:07:45,505
Deal. Sit.

66
00:07:48,265 --> 00:07:50,105
-Let me see.
-I'm still hesitant.

67
00:07:50,185 --> 00:07:52,185
This one is good, but I feel like…

68
00:07:54,185 --> 00:07:56,505
Option two is better.

69
00:08:00,345 --> 00:08:03,625
Finish it and send it to me. Okay, bye.

70
00:08:08,985 --> 00:08:11,545
Are you hungry? Have you eaten?

71
00:08:12,585 --> 00:08:14,545
I already ate. What about you?

72
00:08:14,625 --> 00:08:15,865
I'm full.

73
00:08:18,145 --> 00:08:22,945
Oh, Oon, how many pieces
do we have left in the laundry package?

74
00:08:26,225 --> 00:08:29,385
-I forgot.
-Forgot?

75
00:08:33,784 --> 00:08:34,825
It's okay.

76
00:08:35,985 --> 00:08:38,425
I'll go tomorrow.

77
00:08:42,345 --> 00:08:43,305
You're done with this, right?

78
00:09:06,705 --> 00:09:09,025
Oon, where's the dish soap?

79
00:09:09,105 --> 00:09:10,425
I can't find it.

80
00:09:11,465 --> 00:09:14,425
In the car. I bought it. I'll get it.

81
00:09:25,785 --> 00:09:26,625
Here.

82
00:09:36,705 --> 00:09:38,745
Why did you buy this brand?

83
00:09:38,825 --> 00:09:40,905
I told you I'm allergic to it.

84
00:09:42,145 --> 00:09:45,505
It was on sale. Buy one, get one free.

85
00:09:47,185 --> 00:09:50,145
Seriously? You didn't even check.

86
00:09:56,065 --> 00:09:57,585
And this shampoo.

87
00:09:58,145 --> 00:09:59,945
Why this one?

88
00:10:00,905 --> 00:10:03,425
I thought you used this one.

89
00:10:04,905 --> 00:10:07,465
Yes, I used to.

90
00:10:07,545 --> 00:10:09,985
I can't use it anymore. It makes me itch.

91
00:10:15,105 --> 00:10:16,145
Next time,

92
00:10:16,225 --> 00:10:19,385
I'll handle the household shopping myself.

93
00:10:19,465 --> 00:10:20,905
I won't let you do it anymore.

94
00:10:22,185 --> 00:10:23,705
Nothing you bought can even be used.

95
00:10:25,145 --> 00:10:26,505
I'm sorry.

96
00:10:27,425 --> 00:10:28,705
Don't apologize so often.

97
00:10:29,465 --> 00:10:31,265
It loses its meaning.

98
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:39,785
Forget it this time.

99
00:11:05,265 --> 00:11:06,185
Fun,

100
00:11:06,265 --> 00:11:08,465
help me pick a lipstick shade.

101
00:11:11,065 --> 00:11:12,025
Fun.

102
00:11:13,425 --> 00:11:15,185
Fun, what's wrong with you?

103
00:11:15,265 --> 00:11:18,305
Yeah, you've been so quiet.

104
00:11:18,905 --> 00:11:22,265
-Nothing.
-Nothing? Come on, spill.

105
00:11:22,345 --> 00:11:25,185
When I had problems,
you forced me to talk.

106
00:11:25,265 --> 00:11:28,625
Exactly. And with that face,

107
00:11:28,705 --> 00:11:30,505
you definitely fought
with your girlfriend.

108
00:11:31,665 --> 00:11:32,705
Talk.

109
00:11:34,345 --> 00:11:37,105
Guys, I think Oon has changed.

110
00:11:41,225 --> 00:11:42,305
Tell us.

111
00:11:44,545 --> 00:11:45,585
Well,

112
00:11:46,505 --> 00:11:49,025
she doesn't seem to care
about me like she used to.

113
00:11:49,105 --> 00:11:50,745
The things she used to do for me,

114
00:11:50,825 --> 00:11:53,065
sometimes she forgets,
sometimes she doesn't remember to do them.

115
00:11:53,705 --> 00:11:56,665
Do you think she's seeing someone else?

116
00:11:57,265 --> 00:11:58,505
I don't think so.

117
00:11:58,585 --> 00:12:01,185
Has she been protective
of her phone lately?

118
00:12:01,265 --> 00:12:02,705
No.

119
00:12:02,785 --> 00:12:04,345
Any weird calls

120
00:12:04,425 --> 00:12:05,745
or suspicious chats?

121
00:12:05,825 --> 00:12:06,865
None.

122
00:12:06,945 --> 00:12:10,265
Is she dressing up unusually nice?

123
00:12:10,345 --> 00:12:11,825
She's always pretty.

124
00:12:12,465 --> 00:12:13,585
Is she busy with work?

125
00:12:13,665 --> 00:12:15,705
She's always been busy,

126
00:12:16,305 --> 00:12:18,465
but she's never ignored me like this.

127
00:12:19,145 --> 00:12:21,825
Or maybe I'm just not pretty anymore.

128
00:12:21,905 --> 00:12:23,025
No way.

129
00:12:23,105 --> 00:12:25,465
My friend
is the prettiest in all three worlds.

130
00:12:25,545 --> 00:12:27,945
The most beautiful on Earth.

131
00:12:28,545 --> 00:12:30,825
I don't think looks are the issue.

132
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:33,185
I think your relationship

133
00:12:33,905 --> 00:12:36,065
is hitting a plateau.

134
00:12:36,745 --> 00:12:38,105
A plateau?

135
00:12:39,025 --> 00:12:40,225
What does that mean?

136
00:12:40,745 --> 00:12:44,505
When two people love each other so much,

137
00:12:44,585 --> 00:12:46,425
they reach a peak,

138
00:12:47,065 --> 00:12:48,505
and then things start to fade,

139
00:12:49,065 --> 00:12:52,385
becoming dull and gradually decreasing.

140
00:12:53,985 --> 00:12:56,705
Women usually start

141
00:12:56,785 --> 00:12:59,105
from 0 and build up to 100.

142
00:12:59,185 --> 00:13:01,865
But men start at 100

143
00:13:01,945 --> 00:13:04,945
and drop to 0, just like your girlfriend.

144
00:13:05,545 --> 00:13:07,865
Wait, Aioon is a woman.

145
00:13:08,665 --> 00:13:11,665
Well, same thing.

146
00:13:12,505 --> 00:13:14,585
-Don't stretch it, Jess.
-I'm not stretching!

147
00:13:14,665 --> 00:13:15,865
It's the same thing.

148
00:13:15,945 --> 00:13:16,945
Right?

149
00:13:17,025 --> 00:13:19,665
And if Oon is really like that,

150
00:13:19,745 --> 00:13:21,065
what should I do?

151
00:13:22,105 --> 00:13:23,425
That's not hard.

152
00:13:24,145 --> 00:13:26,225
Start with renovation.

153
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:28,545
Make the space more livable.

154
00:13:29,465 --> 00:13:32,345
You're talking about the house,
not the person.

155
00:13:33,705 --> 00:13:34,865
Same thing.

156
00:13:34,945 --> 00:13:36,065
How?

157
00:13:36,145 --> 00:13:37,145
Listen.

158
00:13:39,865 --> 00:13:42,345
Actually, I think it applies.

159
00:13:43,945 --> 00:13:47,225
Oon once told me our love

160
00:13:47,305 --> 00:13:49,225
is like building a house.

161
00:13:49,305 --> 00:13:51,345
She builds from the front,

162
00:13:51,425 --> 00:13:53,905
I build from the back,

163
00:13:53,985 --> 00:13:56,345
and when we meet in the middle,

164
00:13:56,425 --> 00:13:58,785
it becomes complete.

165
00:13:59,305 --> 00:14:00,945
That sounds good.

166
00:14:01,025 --> 00:14:04,145
No wonder you both work in this field.

167
00:14:06,425 --> 00:14:09,985
Then how do I start renovating?

168
00:14:10,065 --> 00:14:12,025
If it's a good house,

169
00:14:12,105 --> 00:14:14,585
it has to feel comfortable,
physically and emotionally.

170
00:14:14,665 --> 00:14:16,225
In a relationship,

171
00:14:16,305 --> 00:14:19,105
you have to be sweet, not naggy.

172
00:14:19,185 --> 00:14:22,985
Easygoing, low-maintenance, understanding.

173
00:14:25,025 --> 00:14:26,505
Remember this.

174
00:14:26,585 --> 00:14:28,705
No matter what happens,

175
00:14:28,785 --> 00:14:30,345
-it's okay.
-It's okay.

176
00:14:35,785 --> 00:14:36,745
It's okay.

177
00:14:38,545 --> 00:14:39,465
It's okay.

178
00:14:51,425 --> 00:14:55,465
<i>I think your relationship</i>
<i>is hitting a plateau.</i>

179
00:15:01,065 --> 00:15:02,425
A plateau?

180
00:16:25,705 --> 00:16:26,945
<i>-Fun.</i>
-Hmm?

181
00:16:27,465 --> 00:16:29,145
Do you still want this brand?

182
00:16:30,585 --> 00:16:32,065
Oh, yeah.

183
00:16:32,145 --> 00:16:34,185
But the one I want is

184
00:16:34,265 --> 00:16:36,705
-this model. I'll show you.
-Which one?

185
00:16:37,905 --> 00:16:39,505
Here. This one.

186
00:16:39,585 --> 00:16:41,465
You want it? What color?

187
00:16:42,185 --> 00:16:44,865
Wait, let me call Oon first.

188
00:16:46,905 --> 00:16:50,025
PAFUN

189
00:16:55,705 --> 00:16:57,265
-Yes, Fun?
-<i>Oon-oon,</i>

190
00:16:57,345 --> 00:16:59,625
can you help me pick a color?

191
00:16:59,705 --> 00:17:01,305
A watch?

192
00:17:01,385 --> 00:17:03,505
Yeah, a couple's watch.

193
00:17:03,585 --> 00:17:04,704
-This one--
-<i>Nu's calling.</i>

194
00:17:05,905 --> 00:17:07,585
Hold on, Fun. I'll call you back.

195
00:17:08,424 --> 00:17:10,745
But this--

196
00:17:13,184 --> 00:17:15,505
Wait. I'll wait for her to call back.

197
00:17:17,025 --> 00:17:19,865
Fun, did your girlfriend call back?

198
00:17:19,944 --> 00:17:21,545
She needs to go soon.

199
00:17:22,184 --> 00:17:23,545
Not yet.

200
00:17:24,745 --> 00:17:26,224
It's fine. I won't get it.

201
00:17:36,385 --> 00:17:40,545
DEAL CLOSED. TIME TO CELEBRATE.

202
00:17:40,625 --> 00:17:42,105
You look happy.

203
00:17:47,865 --> 00:17:49,545
Please don't change.

204
00:18:31,825 --> 00:18:32,865
<i>It's okay…</i>

205
00:18:33,665 --> 00:18:37,145
<i>Pafun, it's okay. It's okay…</i>

206
00:18:39,305 --> 00:18:40,505
<i>It's okay…</i>

207
00:18:58,345 --> 00:19:00,625
PAFUN

208
00:19:02,225 --> 00:19:04,305
-Yes, Fun?
-<i>Oon-Oon.</i>

209
00:19:04,385 --> 00:19:06,225
Are you free? Can you talk?

210
00:19:06,825 --> 00:19:07,865
I can.

211
00:19:09,185 --> 00:19:12,745
Could you buy me the tom yum noodles
from in front of your office this evening?

212
00:19:12,825 --> 00:19:15,625
Of course.
Extra shrimp, like usual, right?

213
00:19:16,185 --> 00:19:17,025
<i>Yes.</i>

214
00:19:17,105 --> 00:19:19,825
Okay. Do you want anything else?

215
00:19:20,705 --> 00:19:21,905
No, that's all.

216
00:19:22,425 --> 00:19:24,745
Are you going to eat noodles with me too,

217
00:19:24,825 --> 00:19:27,105
or do you want me to get you something?

218
00:19:28,585 --> 00:19:31,145
It's okay. I'll just eat noodles with you.

219
00:19:31,225 --> 00:19:33,945
Okay. See you at home tonight.

220
00:19:34,025 --> 00:19:35,265
See you.

221
00:19:35,345 --> 00:19:36,825
Okay. Bye-bye.

222
00:19:40,425 --> 00:19:42,225
Oon's still the same.

223
00:19:42,865 --> 00:19:44,225
Maybe I was overthinking it.

224
00:19:49,305 --> 00:19:51,465
Oon, where's Fifa?

225
00:19:51,545 --> 00:19:53,225
He's in a team meeting.

226
00:19:54,305 --> 00:19:56,625
Really?
Are you tied up with anything right now?

227
00:19:57,305 --> 00:19:58,545
No.

228
00:19:58,625 --> 00:20:01,185
Then come meet the consultant with me.

229
00:20:01,265 --> 00:20:04,465
Bring the company's sample work too.
I want the complex projects.

230
00:20:04,545 --> 00:20:06,985
Sure. Give me 20 minutes.

231
00:20:08,105 --> 00:20:09,625
Then I'll head out first.

232
00:20:09,705 --> 00:20:12,705
I've scheduled the consultant
for 4 p.m. Hurry and follow me there.

233
00:20:12,785 --> 00:20:13,865
Okay.

234
00:21:03,665 --> 00:21:04,745
Boo!

235
00:21:11,705 --> 00:21:12,705
Are you tired?

236
00:21:12,785 --> 00:21:14,545
Very tired.

237
00:21:18,785 --> 00:21:19,865
Better now?

238
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:21,585
All better.

239
00:21:34,985 --> 00:21:38,225
-I missed you so much.
-I missed you too.

240
00:21:38,305 --> 00:21:40,705
Let me put my bag down first.

241
00:21:47,065 --> 00:21:49,465
-Where is it?
-What?

242
00:21:50,065 --> 00:21:51,305
My noodles.

243
00:21:52,905 --> 00:21:53,905
Oh.

244
00:21:54,905 --> 00:21:57,145
Are they still in the car?
Then I'll go get them.

245
00:22:02,825 --> 00:22:03,865
I forgot.

246
00:22:05,425 --> 00:22:06,505
Forgot?

247
00:22:07,465 --> 00:22:09,305
What do you want to eat?
I'll order it for you.

248
00:22:10,065 --> 00:22:11,025
No need.

249
00:22:14,625 --> 00:22:18,065
Fun, I'm sorry.

250
00:22:19,985 --> 00:22:23,225
I told you before, didn't I?
Don't use apologies so casually.

251
00:22:23,745 --> 00:22:26,545
You say sorry so much
that now it feels meaningless.

252
00:22:28,265 --> 00:22:29,305
Fun…

253
00:22:32,505 --> 00:22:33,465
It's weird, isn't it?

254
00:22:34,185 --> 00:22:35,985
Ever since we got married,

255
00:22:36,065 --> 00:22:38,385
I'm always the first thing you forget.

256
00:22:39,545 --> 00:22:42,305
Before, if I said I wanted chestnuts,

257
00:22:42,385 --> 00:22:44,345
you'd drive me all the way to Yaowarat.

258
00:22:44,425 --> 00:22:46,025
If I said I wanted river prawns,

259
00:22:46,105 --> 00:22:48,585
you'd drive me all the way to Ayutthaya.
But now what?

260
00:22:48,665 --> 00:22:50,065
Just one bag of noodles

261
00:22:50,145 --> 00:22:52,705
right outside your office,
not even 100 meters away, and you forgot.

262
00:22:53,345 --> 00:22:54,225
Fun,

263
00:22:54,825 --> 00:22:56,345
it's just one bag of noodles.

264
00:22:56,425 --> 00:22:58,945
It's not just that, Oon.
It's more than that.

265
00:22:59,025 --> 00:23:00,345
There are all the household things too.

266
00:23:00,425 --> 00:23:03,865
The things I told you I can't use,
that I'm allergic to. You never care.

267
00:23:04,665 --> 00:23:06,865
-I do care, Fun.
-Do you?

268
00:23:08,625 --> 00:23:11,745
And then there's how you are outside.
You're cheerful and having fun,

269
00:23:11,825 --> 00:23:13,105
but when you come home, you're tired.

270
00:23:13,185 --> 00:23:15,865
You either play games
or watch TV by yourself.

271
00:23:16,945 --> 00:23:18,185
Tell me honestly, Oon,

272
00:23:18,265 --> 00:23:20,105
where exactly am I in your life?

273
00:23:20,945 --> 00:23:21,945
Fun…

274
00:23:22,025 --> 00:23:23,785
And then about your life,

275
00:23:23,865 --> 00:23:26,465
before, I was always
the first person to know everything.

276
00:23:26,985 --> 00:23:27,985
But now…

277
00:23:30,265 --> 00:23:31,785
maybe I'm the last to know.

278
00:23:33,505 --> 00:23:36,745
If you're going to neglect and forget me,
then maybe just forget that I'm even here.

279
00:23:36,825 --> 00:23:37,705
Fun,

280
00:23:37,785 --> 00:23:39,905
can you calm down?
This is getting out of hand.

281
00:23:39,985 --> 00:23:41,705
I think you're overthinking it.

282
00:23:41,785 --> 00:23:44,825
I'm overthinking?
Or am I just being selfish too?

283
00:23:48,945 --> 00:23:52,505
Have you ever looked back at yourself
and seen how much you've changed?

284
00:23:54,265 --> 00:23:55,145
Fun,

285
00:23:55,665 --> 00:23:58,465
let's wait until you calm down first.
Then we can talk. That'd be better.

286
00:23:59,225 --> 00:24:00,705
Better than what, Oon?

287
00:24:00,785 --> 00:24:02,465
Better than what?

288
00:24:03,105 --> 00:24:05,345
Better than what? Tell me.

289
00:24:05,425 --> 00:24:07,225
Better than fighting like this.

290
00:24:15,545 --> 00:24:17,025
Why are you walking away again?

291
00:24:23,065 --> 00:24:25,825
Every time we fight now,

292
00:24:25,905 --> 00:24:29,025
all you do is walk away from the problem
and leave me here alone.

293
00:24:29,705 --> 00:24:30,945
If that's how it's going to be,

294
00:24:32,865 --> 00:24:34,425
we should live our own lives.

295
00:24:45,145 --> 00:24:47,265
What do you mean, live our own lives?

296
00:24:49,465 --> 00:24:50,785
I mean…

297
00:24:51,985 --> 00:24:53,305
we should break up.

298
00:24:57,665 --> 00:25:00,545
Are you sure you want to say that?

299
00:25:06,785 --> 00:25:10,145
Then fine. Have it your way,
if that's what you really want.

300
00:27:13,545 --> 00:27:14,585
What's up?

301
00:27:14,665 --> 00:27:17,705
Are you busy or something?
You took forever to answer.

302
00:27:18,425 --> 00:27:19,985
No, I can talk.

303
00:27:20,065 --> 00:27:22,905
So, Anda and I are in Bangkok now.

304
00:27:22,985 --> 00:27:24,385
And we'll open

305
00:27:24,465 --> 00:27:26,505
the cafe in less than a week.

306
00:27:27,585 --> 00:27:28,985
Congratulations.

307
00:27:29,065 --> 00:27:32,305
Lin and her girlfriend just got back
to Thailand a couple of days ago.

308
00:27:32,385 --> 00:27:34,705
When are you free? We should all meet up.

309
00:27:36,105 --> 00:27:37,065
Well,

310
00:27:37,705 --> 00:27:39,145
any day's fine.

311
00:27:42,105 --> 00:27:43,025
Oon,

312
00:27:43,945 --> 00:27:47,105
is something wrong?
Why does your voice sound off?

313
00:27:47,705 --> 00:27:50,265
No, I'm fine.

314
00:27:50,785 --> 00:27:53,745
Don't lie to me.
Something's definitely wrong.

315
00:27:53,825 --> 00:27:56,305
Where are you? And where's Pafun?

316
00:28:01,745 --> 00:28:04,105
<i>See? You definitely fought with Pafun.</i>

317
00:28:04,905 --> 00:28:06,065
Where are you?

318
00:28:06,145 --> 00:28:07,705
Are you coming to the cafe,

319
00:28:07,785 --> 00:28:10,665
or do you want me to come to your house?
I'll get to see Pafun too.

320
00:28:10,745 --> 00:28:13,785
No need. I'll come to your cafe.

321
00:28:17,065 --> 00:28:18,665
I'll send you the location.

322
00:28:18,745 --> 00:28:20,065
SEND LOCATION

323
00:28:20,145 --> 00:28:22,265
Tap it and see how long it would take you
to get there. I've already sent it.

324
00:28:26,545 --> 00:28:30,185
THE JOURNEY TAKES 47 MINUTES

325
00:28:31,705 --> 00:28:32,945
Forty-seven minutes.

326
00:28:33,785 --> 00:28:35,145
Fine,

327
00:28:35,225 --> 00:28:37,185
I'm adding traffic
and rounding it up to 50.

328
00:28:37,265 --> 00:28:38,465
If you're not here

329
00:28:38,545 --> 00:28:40,985
in 50 minutes, I'm going to your house.

330
00:28:54,025 --> 00:28:55,905
There you are.

331
00:28:57,025 --> 00:28:58,985
-Come here.
-Sit down, troublemaker.

332
00:28:59,505 --> 00:29:01,545
-Sit right here.
-Come here.

333
00:29:04,185 --> 00:29:05,465
And look at that face.

334
00:29:05,545 --> 00:29:08,065
Plate. Coffee.

335
00:29:14,945 --> 00:29:17,785
Oon, can you stop making that face?

336
00:29:17,865 --> 00:29:20,265
You look like a cat
that hasn't been fed wet food.

337
00:29:22,905 --> 00:29:24,225
It's true.

338
00:29:29,185 --> 00:29:31,985
So everyone's here.

339
00:29:32,705 --> 00:29:34,065
Only Baibua's missing.

340
00:29:35,425 --> 00:29:37,665
She couldn't make it.
She's stuck working in Phuket.

341
00:29:37,745 --> 00:29:39,985
But she told me
to send her love to everyone.

342
00:29:41,425 --> 00:29:43,105
Thank you.

343
00:29:46,665 --> 00:29:49,465
Alright, let's start
with your problem first.

344
00:29:50,105 --> 00:29:51,865
Once everyone found out,

345
00:29:51,945 --> 00:29:54,345
we all gathered here
without even planning it.

346
00:29:59,105 --> 00:30:00,945
Thanks, guys.

347
00:30:03,185 --> 00:30:06,465
So, what happened?

348
00:30:12,745 --> 00:30:14,545
I just…

349
00:30:16,705 --> 00:30:18,945
forgot to buy her noodles.

350
00:30:23,425 --> 00:30:25,225
I don't think it's just that.

351
00:30:26,585 --> 00:30:29,105
I mean, Pafun's not
that unreasonable, right?

352
00:30:29,185 --> 00:30:31,145
-Right.
-Yeah.

353
00:30:33,665 --> 00:30:34,505
Well…

354
00:30:35,505 --> 00:30:38,505
She said I've changed,

355
00:30:39,145 --> 00:30:40,545
that I don't pay attention anymore,

356
00:30:41,065 --> 00:30:44,865
that I forget little things about her.

357
00:30:46,105 --> 00:30:48,785
Well, you do forget things, right?

358
00:30:50,585 --> 00:30:51,705
Sometimes.

359
00:30:51,785 --> 00:30:52,705
See?

360
00:30:54,305 --> 00:30:56,465
But I didn't mean to.

361
00:30:57,065 --> 00:30:59,705
Well, it was just

362
00:31:00,425 --> 00:31:02,745
the shampoo brand she said

363
00:31:03,305 --> 00:31:05,065
makes her itch

364
00:31:05,705 --> 00:31:08,545
and the dish soap
she said she's allergic to.

365
00:31:12,065 --> 00:31:14,665
That's not "just."

366
00:31:15,985 --> 00:31:19,425
Those are exactly the little things
you're supposed to pay attention to.

367
00:31:28,785 --> 00:31:30,225
I'm really in the wrong.

368
00:31:31,425 --> 00:31:32,705
Fun even broke up with me.

369
00:31:35,785 --> 00:31:37,145
She broke up with you?

370
00:31:37,945 --> 00:31:40,745
And you didn't even try
to make it up to her?

371
00:31:41,825 --> 00:31:42,785
Oh?

372
00:31:42,865 --> 00:31:46,465
I was hurt too, so I just left the house.

373
00:31:48,745 --> 00:31:50,945
So you just left her home alone like that?

374
00:31:51,505 --> 00:31:52,945
Is this going to work?

375
00:31:54,665 --> 00:31:58,145
Oon, you can't leave her alone
to overthink everything like that.

376
00:31:59,945 --> 00:32:03,025
Then what am I supposed to do?

377
00:32:07,825 --> 00:32:09,865
Alright, first of all,

378
00:32:09,945 --> 00:32:11,505
fix yourself first.

379
00:32:11,585 --> 00:32:13,225
Do you have problems right now?

380
00:32:13,305 --> 00:32:15,985
Work? Personal stuff?

381
00:32:16,065 --> 00:32:17,305
Anything?

382
00:32:20,225 --> 00:32:21,505
Nothing really.

383
00:32:22,905 --> 00:32:24,625
I'm just tired.

384
00:32:25,385 --> 00:32:26,625
Work's been heavy,

385
00:32:27,825 --> 00:32:28,785
and

386
00:32:29,425 --> 00:32:32,145
I have goals I'm trying to reach.

387
00:32:32,225 --> 00:32:33,105
Oon,

388
00:32:33,185 --> 00:32:36,985
you can't be such a workaholic
that your marriage falls apart.

389
00:32:37,065 --> 00:32:40,345
You're married now.
You have to take care of her feelings too.

390
00:32:40,945 --> 00:32:44,385
But it's because I care about her,
because I think about her,

391
00:32:45,585 --> 00:32:48,225
that's why I have to try harder.

392
00:32:48,305 --> 00:32:49,585
Well,

393
00:32:50,105 --> 00:32:53,865
I'm trying to qualify
as a professional engineer,

394
00:32:54,465 --> 00:32:57,185
so I've been taking on more projects
to build my portfolio.

395
00:32:59,305 --> 00:33:02,745
More importantly, I want to move forward

396
00:33:02,825 --> 00:33:04,545
and make more money

397
00:33:04,625 --> 00:33:07,065
because I want
to make her dream come true.

398
00:33:09,345 --> 00:33:10,545
What dream?

399
00:33:12,665 --> 00:33:16,265
Fun once told me she wants to open

400
00:33:16,345 --> 00:33:19,385
her own small
interior design company someday.

401
00:33:20,305 --> 00:33:24,225
I want her to be able
to fully pursue that dream,

402
00:33:24,305 --> 00:33:27,745
so I planned to take responsibility
for all the household expenses.

403
00:33:28,265 --> 00:33:30,665
That way,
she wouldn't have to worry about anything.

404
00:33:32,385 --> 00:33:34,025
Sugar mama.

405
00:33:37,865 --> 00:33:40,385
Did you ever tell Pafun any of this?

406
00:33:41,505 --> 00:33:43,585
Well, no.

407
00:33:44,825 --> 00:33:46,625
I wanted it to be a surprise.

408
00:33:46,705 --> 00:33:48,025
There you go.

409
00:33:48,105 --> 00:33:49,905
You wanted to surprise her,

410
00:33:49,985 --> 00:33:52,865
and instead you got surprised yourself.
Happy now?

411
00:33:54,305 --> 00:33:55,145
Come on.

412
00:33:55,225 --> 00:33:58,145
Look at her. Look at our friend.

413
00:34:04,105 --> 00:34:08,945
Oon, a marriage needs communication.

414
00:34:09,025 --> 00:34:11,625
If you don't say anything,
how is she supposed to know?

415
00:34:12,225 --> 00:34:13,145
Yeah.

416
00:34:13,225 --> 00:34:15,905
You can't let her overthink like this.

417
00:34:18,145 --> 00:34:19,585
And most importantly,

418
00:34:19,665 --> 00:34:23,145
inconsistency is
the scariest thing of all.

419
00:34:23,225 --> 00:34:24,385
In the end,

420
00:34:24,465 --> 00:34:27,425
it slowly destroys
the other person's feelings.

421
00:34:27,505 --> 00:34:30,105
Before you even realize it,
everything might already be broken.

422
00:34:31,304 --> 00:34:32,225
So,

423
00:34:32,304 --> 00:34:35,705
don't change from the person you were
on the first day you started dating her.

424
00:34:36,585 --> 00:34:37,545
Exactly.

425
00:34:38,065 --> 00:34:41,625
However attentive you were on day one,
you need to stay that attentive.

426
00:34:49,505 --> 00:34:51,225
If you understand that now,

427
00:34:52,025 --> 00:34:53,744
then go back and clear things up with her.

428
00:34:58,945 --> 00:35:01,145
But I don't even know how to start.

429
00:35:02,345 --> 00:35:04,105
You want us to start it for you?

430
00:35:05,025 --> 00:35:05,905
Should we just go?

431
00:35:05,985 --> 00:35:08,065
Yeah, let's do it.

432
00:35:08,145 --> 00:35:09,585
-Let's go.
-Go.

433
00:35:09,665 --> 00:35:10,825
Stop.

434
00:35:11,665 --> 00:35:13,265
Don't.

435
00:35:13,345 --> 00:35:15,065
I'll handle it myself.

436
00:35:15,145 --> 00:35:17,665
Can you really?

437
00:35:17,745 --> 00:35:20,305
Or are you just going
to come back and cry to us again?

438
00:35:20,385 --> 00:35:22,265
Let her handle it herself.

439
00:35:22,345 --> 00:35:24,265
-Let's drink.
-Cheers.

440
00:35:24,345 --> 00:35:25,865
-Cheers.
-Go handle it yourself.

441
00:36:00,385 --> 00:36:01,825
Don't turn on the light.

442
00:36:13,585 --> 00:36:14,585
Fun…

443
00:36:23,905 --> 00:36:25,465
Did you come back to pack your things?

444
00:36:27,745 --> 00:36:29,585
I didn't come back to pack anything.

445
00:36:45,385 --> 00:36:46,825
Let me ask you honestly, Oon.

446
00:36:47,865 --> 00:36:49,105
Right now,

447
00:36:49,705 --> 00:36:51,345
do you still love me?

448
00:36:53,425 --> 00:36:54,505
Of course I do.

449
00:36:56,105 --> 00:36:58,225
Is this how people
who love each other treat each other?

450
00:36:59,185 --> 00:37:01,625
You never keep any of your promises.

451
00:37:02,545 --> 00:37:04,865
In the end, you're all talk.

452
00:37:06,465 --> 00:37:09,585
You don't love me, Oon. You love yourself.

453
00:37:12,145 --> 00:37:13,425
Love myself?

454
00:37:16,105 --> 00:37:17,665
Everything I've been doing,

455
00:37:18,305 --> 00:37:20,385
does that look like loving myself, Fun?

456
00:37:23,065 --> 00:37:25,025
I've been working this hard,

457
00:37:25,825 --> 00:37:29,265
taking every project I can
because I need the portfolio.

458
00:37:32,225 --> 00:37:34,585
I want to move up and become
a licensed professional engineer.

459
00:37:35,985 --> 00:37:37,785
I want to be able to support you.

460
00:37:39,625 --> 00:37:41,905
I want to take care of all the expenses
in this house,

461
00:37:42,945 --> 00:37:44,825
because I remember…

462
00:37:44,905 --> 00:37:48,545
I remember you telling me that you want
to open your own small company someday.

463
00:37:48,625 --> 00:37:51,585
You want to do creative work
that makes you happy.

464
00:37:57,185 --> 00:37:59,145
I thought that when the day comes
and you're ready,

465
00:38:00,705 --> 00:38:02,025
you'd be able to do it.

466
00:38:02,745 --> 00:38:06,585
And you could do it fully
without having to worry about anything.

467
00:38:12,345 --> 00:38:15,345
I was wrong for never telling you.

468
00:38:16,105 --> 00:38:18,825
I'm sorry for neglecting things.

469
00:38:18,905 --> 00:38:21,585
Sorry for forgetting,
for not paying enough attention,

470
00:38:21,665 --> 00:38:23,305
sorry that I changed.

471
00:38:26,785 --> 00:38:27,905
But this is

472
00:38:29,865 --> 00:38:31,785
all I'm capable of doing for you.

473
00:38:35,105 --> 00:38:36,945
I really did my best.

474
00:38:51,905 --> 00:38:53,745
Oon…

475
00:39:01,545 --> 00:39:02,745
I'm sorry.

476
00:39:05,065 --> 00:39:07,105
If you were thinking of doing all this,
why didn't you tell me?

477
00:39:07,665 --> 00:39:09,745
Why did you keep everything to yourself?

478
00:39:16,705 --> 00:39:18,865
Because I love you.

479
00:39:33,225 --> 00:39:34,945
I'm sorry, Oon.

480
00:39:35,545 --> 00:39:37,105
I really am.

481
00:39:40,265 --> 00:39:41,345
It's okay.

482
00:39:42,185 --> 00:39:43,265
It's okay.

483
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:48,465
It's okay.

484
00:39:51,545 --> 00:39:52,745
It's okay.

485
00:39:54,425 --> 00:39:55,785
I'm sorry too.

486
00:39:57,465 --> 00:39:59,425
I'm sorry I never told you.

487
00:40:02,345 --> 00:40:06,105
I wanted to make it happen first
and then tell you.

488
00:40:11,025 --> 00:40:14,185
I was wrong too. I never asked.

489
00:40:15,145 --> 00:40:17,345
I just assumed things.

490
00:40:21,505 --> 00:40:25,345
From now on, we'll talk about everything.

491
00:40:28,145 --> 00:40:29,665
I'll trust you.

492
00:40:30,985 --> 00:40:33,785
If there's something I don't understand,
I'll ask.

493
00:40:36,985 --> 00:40:40,145
From now on, no matter what I do,

494
00:40:40,745 --> 00:40:42,665
I'll tell you.

495
00:40:43,225 --> 00:40:45,185
I won't wait for you to ask.

496
00:41:48,345 --> 00:41:50,025
-Oon-Oon.
-Hmm?

497
00:41:56,505 --> 00:41:58,625
If one day in the future we fight again,

498
00:42:00,505 --> 00:42:02,145
I want you to know something.

499
00:42:03,425 --> 00:42:05,065
When I'm sulking,

500
00:42:05,785 --> 00:42:07,345
it means I want you to coax me.

501
00:42:09,385 --> 00:42:11,185
When I'm crying,

502
00:42:11,825 --> 00:42:13,625
it means I want you to come hold me.

503
00:42:15,465 --> 00:42:16,985
And when I tell you to go,

504
00:42:18,265 --> 00:42:21,465
I don't really want you to leave.
Do you understand?

505
00:42:23,145 --> 00:42:25,065
I understand.

506
00:42:26,865 --> 00:42:28,505
But honestly, it'd be better

507
00:42:29,105 --> 00:42:31,385
if we just didn't fight at all, right?

508
00:42:36,585 --> 00:42:40,585
And if I want some encouragement,

509
00:42:42,105 --> 00:42:43,345
what should I do?

510
00:42:45,545 --> 00:42:47,185
Where do you want it?

511
00:42:50,425 --> 00:42:51,585
Here.

512
00:42:57,025 --> 00:42:57,985
Here.

513
00:43:01,145 --> 00:43:02,145
Here.

514
00:43:06,265 --> 00:43:07,225
And here too.

515
00:43:08,785 --> 00:43:10,345
Aren't you tired anymore?

516
00:43:11,425 --> 00:43:14,785
If it's this kind of tired,
I'll fight to the death.

517
00:45:02,665 --> 00:45:03,785
<i>Are you okay?</i>

518
00:45:03,865 --> 00:45:06,545
Everyone's been worried about you,

519
00:45:06,625 --> 00:45:08,665
so I volunteered to call and check.

520
00:45:08,745 --> 00:45:10,665
We made up already.

521
00:45:11,185 --> 00:45:12,705
Thanks so much, all of you.

522
00:45:14,425 --> 00:45:15,505
<i>It's okay.</i>

523
00:45:15,585 --> 00:45:17,985
<i>Now that you two are good again,</i>
<i>we can relax.</i>

524
00:45:18,065 --> 00:45:19,465
Oh, by the way,

525
00:45:19,985 --> 00:45:22,425
next week, I'm opening my new cafe.

526
00:45:22,505 --> 00:45:25,145
<i>I want you and Pafun to come.</i>

527
00:45:25,225 --> 00:45:28,625
I don't know when all of us
will get to gather like this again.

528
00:45:28,705 --> 00:45:31,985
Once everything's settled,

529
00:45:33,505 --> 00:45:36,025
Gorya and I will head back to Chiang Mai.

530
00:45:37,025 --> 00:45:40,025
Then who's going to take care of the cafe?

531
00:45:40,105 --> 00:45:43,345
Probably my sister.

532
00:45:45,105 --> 00:45:47,305
-So…
-<i>Yeah.</i>

533
00:45:47,385 --> 00:45:48,665
We'll definitely be there.

534
00:45:48,745 --> 00:45:51,025
Okay. See you next week.

535
00:46:03,665 --> 00:46:05,065
-Fun.
-Yes?

536
00:46:05,145 --> 00:46:08,145
Do you remember my high school friends?

537
00:46:08,225 --> 00:46:09,825
Gorya and Anda?

538
00:46:11,145 --> 00:46:12,345
Of course.

539
00:46:13,065 --> 00:46:16,025
Next Sunday, Gorya and Anda

540
00:46:16,105 --> 00:46:19,105
are having opening
their new cafe near Sathorn.

541
00:46:19,185 --> 00:46:22,425
All our friends are getting together.
Come with me.

542
00:46:23,665 --> 00:46:24,665
Of course.

543
00:46:26,985 --> 00:46:27,865
You want some?

544
00:48:07,825 --> 00:48:09,345
-Oon.
-Hmm?

545
00:48:09,425 --> 00:48:10,865
I want to have a baby.

546
00:48:11,705 --> 00:48:12,745
Huh?

547
00:48:17,145 --> 00:48:18,065
You really don't remember me?

548
00:48:19,905 --> 00:48:21,265
Fun was my first love, you know.

549
00:48:22,545 --> 00:48:24,105
Oh, Krit.

550
00:48:24,785 --> 00:48:27,745
Fun, I already ordered
your favorite chocolate cake for you.

551
00:48:27,825 --> 00:48:31,625
<i>Our chocolate lava cake</i>
<i>is very popular among couples.</i>

552
00:49:02,385 --> 00:49:03,345
